title: The wild Albanian island where the Trumps want to build a luxury hotel
subhed: Once a Cold War military outpost, this Mediterranean island, known for its lush vegetation and turquoise waters, had long been left abandoned. But Jared Kushner saw its tourism potential. Leveraging his network that blurs geopolitics and private interests, Donald Trump's son-in-law easily secured Albanian approval to build a luxury hotel complex in the heart of this protected landscape.
